# Testing

## Structure

- One test file per source file: `color.odin` -> `test_color.odin`, `palette.odin` -> `test_palette.odin`
- Test files live in the same package directory as the code they test
- Test procedures use the `@(test)` attribute and take `t: ^testing.T`

## Naming

Test procedure names follow `test_<subject>_<behavior>`:

```odin
test_color_init_defaults
test_parse_hex_valid_lowercase
test_palette_add_rejects_when_full
test_contrast_ratio_black_on_white
```

## Assertions

- `testing.expect_value(t, got, expected)` for equality checks
- `testing.expect(t, condition)` for boolean conditions
- Test both happy path and edge cases (invalid input, boundaries, empty collections)

## What to Test

- `color/` — round-trip conversions, boundary values, invalid hex, harmony counts, contrast ratios, CVD matrices
- `data/` — history ring-buffer wraparound, palette add/remove at capacity, palette persistence round-trips
- Do NOT test `ui/` or root package procedures — they depend on Raylib initialization

## Running

```
odin test color/
odin test data/
```
